but those require separate hoplite-* format modules; meaningful hoplite-core coverage should use MapPropertySource, SystemPropertiesPropertySource, EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource, or built-in .props/.properties parsing unless the workflow intentionally adds a format module.\",\n    \"Version 3.0 changes environment variable path conventions, so tests that choose to exercise EnvironmentVariablesPropertySource must set variables in the new upper-case underscore style; this is optional test design, not required setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0318bb52fab49048016a3f7ec920988195a35d8cbcfd66a909\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 153, "output": 1109, "cacheRead": 51712, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52974, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782546106595, "responseId": "resp_0318bb52fab49048016a3f7ebb53d88195a24c8e3ba5d72981"}, "toolResults": []}
